OL,6,FHe says he would rather farm without a
OL,7,Fpayment before that. Mr Davies said:
OL,8,F"It'll be tough but that's it, I'll
OL,9,Fget on with it, it's tough for
OL,10,Feveryone in the world."
OL,12,FThe next generation of farmers is also
OL,13,Fconcerned about what will happen to
OL,14,Fthe sector in the coming years.
OL,15,FAgriculture college students Mali
OL,16,FEllis-Roberts and Ella Jones say
OL,17,Feveryone relies on the rural community
OL,18,Fto feed their families.
